{
  "texts": [
    "Let us now concentrate on any places where the two wavefronts meet tangentially.",
    "These correspond to ∇t (θ) = 0.",
    "At these places the normals to the two wavefronts are the same.",
    "Since normals to the wavefront are light rays, ∇t (θ) = 0 corresponds to light rays travelling out from the source with a wavefront and then down the sky to the observer.",
    "Moreover, t (θ) at these sky locations is the light travel time, apart from an additive constant."
  ]
}